In [30]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
car_crashes = sns.load_dataset("car_crashes")
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.barplot(x='abbrev', y='total', data=car_crashes, palette='coolwarm')
plt.xlabel('Abbreviation')
plt.ylabel('Total Car Crashes')
plt.title('Total Car Crashes by State Abbreviation')
plt.xticks(rotation=90)
plt.show()
In [ ]:
Inference: The graph reveals that among the total number of crashes in each state, the highest crash rates are observed in three states: ND, SC, and WV.
